Like I said, I normally wouldn’t give this moral panic diatribe a second blink. But Alabama is one of 34 states attempting to pass anti-trans bills. 8/

But back to mother. Mother is a relational term we give to people who take care of their children. It’s not biological at all. I know plenty of mothers who have never given birth. And what about the folks who give birth, but give their kids up for adoption? 7/

“Birthing people” doesn’t take away from you or your role, it just includes the very real (like I promise you they exist. I could put you in touch if you’d like) people that benefit from these maternal mortality boards you mentioned. 6/

Let’s talk about moms. I’m happy you feel celebrated using the word “mother.” I have fought for three years to try to be one myself and hope one day to wear that name proudly. But some folks who birth kids don’t feel included in that word. 5/

For starters, transgender is not considered a disorder according to WHO in 2019 (written after DSM 5.) And tbh I wouldn’t expect you to know that. It’s ok you don’t know that. But it’s reason number 675834 that we shouldn’t take medical advice from columnists or legislators. 4/

They’re your neighbors, your kids’ classmates, your Target checkout person. This fake moral outrage gets clicks and maybe a pat on the back from your pastor. But it further pushes trans folks back into the recesses and emboldens hate and violence against them. 3/

This medically inaccurate, pearl-clutching speculation does nothing but stigmatize folks in our state who literally fight for their right to exist each day. I guess you may not have met a trans person before. That’s ok. But I promise you they exist. 2/
